Here's a complete implementation:

```csharp
// In Program.cs

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Configure max request body size (e.g., 15MB to allow overhead beyond 10MB file limit)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(options =>
{
    options.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 15 * 1024 * 1024;
});

builder.Services.AddAntiforgery();

var app = builder.Build();

app.UseAntiforgery();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    const long maxFileSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10MB

    string[] allowedTypes = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    string[] allowedExtensions = [".jpg", ".jpeg", ".png"];

    if (!allowedTypes.Contains(file.ContentType.ToLowerInvariant()))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    var extension = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (!allowedExtensions.Contains(extension))
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    if (file.Length > maxFileSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File size exceeds 10MB limit.");

    var uploadsPath = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsPath);

    // Use a random name to avoid collisions and path traversal
    var savedName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{extension}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsPath, savedName);

    await using var stream = new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Create);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName = savedName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery(); // Remove this line if you want CSRF protection on the endpoint

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **Kestrel limit** — Set higher than 10MB to account for multipart overhead.
- **Validation** — Checks both `ContentType` and file extension.
- **Safe filenames** — Uses `Guid.NewGuid()` to prevent path traversal and collisions.
- **Antiforgery** — `.DisableAntiforgery()` is added since API clients typically use token auth instead. Remove it if your clients send the antiforgery token (e.g., Razor Pages forms).

If you're behind IIS, also add to `web.config`:

```xml
<system.webServer>
  <security>
    <requestFiltering>
      <requestLimits maxAllowedContentLength="15728640" />
    </requestFiltering>
  </security>
</system.webServer>
```
